-- Chilean Stocks: Banco de Chile, Enersis SA and SACI Falabella
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-27T20:51:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/chilean-stocks-banco-de-chile-enersis-sa-and-saci-falabella.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index rose 0.2 percent to 4,226.08. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index gained 0.6 percent to 2,441.09.  Banco de Chile  (CHILE CC) advanced 0.7 percent to 73.78
pesos, its second day of gains. The country’s second-largest
bank will seek shareholder approval at a March 22 meeting to
distribute 70 percent of last year’s profit in dividends, or
about 2.98 pesos per share. Banco de Chile will propose paying
out the remaining 30 percent of profit in new shares at a rate
of 0.02 new stock per existing share, according to a regulatory
filing.  Enersis SA (ENERSIS)   rose 0.9 percent to 173.71 pesos.
The Latin American unit of  Spain ’s Endesa SA was reiterated
“buy” at Citigroup Inc., according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  SACI Falabella (FALAB)   rose 1 percent to 4,241.6 pesos,
its second day of gains. Investors should consider buying shares
of Chile’s largest retailer by market value as selling pressure
from local pension funds recedes, Banco de Credito & Inversiones
said in an e-mailed note to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
